(secondQuint)Involvement of Patients and Relatives in the Course of Cancer Disease.

 The study aim to evaluate the effect and the benefit of the program.

 First the patients psychosocial well-being is assessed in a survey (EORTC, POMS, WHO-5 well-being index) Then their relatives psychosocial well-being is assessed in a survey (Ad hoc questions, POMS and WHO-5 well-being index) The effect is also assessed in qualitative interviews with patients and their relatives.

 The rehabilitation course is investigated in qualitative observations and interviews.

